message.content:
We must “collapse” the many transactions and add up only those whose type is exactly “Administrative Expenses.” In our solution we manually extracted those rows and added their “amount” values. (A quick outline of the work below shows that we went row‐by‐row, found the “Administrative Expenses” rows, and then summed each amount.)

For example (showing, not all details):

• On 2024‑01‑01 “Administrative Expenses” you see 37,969.92  
• On 2024‑01‑02 there are three “Administrative Expenses” rows: 45,081.08, 36,805.48, and 44,888.15  
• Then on 2024‑01‑03 there are three rows: 18,776.65, 32,203.00 and 6,540.08  
• … (and many more rows follow)  
• Up to the last “Administrative Expenses” row on 2024‑01‑30 amounting to 22,841.68

When we sum all these “Administrative Expenses” amounts throughout the period we arrive at a total of 1,776,178.15. 

Thus the final administrative expenses item on the income statement is 1,776,178.15.

The answer in the required json format is:

------------------------------------------------

{"solution": {"Administrative Expenses": "1776178.15"} }
